&nbsp;
The attack, which took place in the concert hall located in Krasnogorsk, northwest of the Russian capital, is the bloodiest in Russia in the last twenty years and the most bloody claimed by Isis in Europe. According to the Russian Ministry for Emergency Situations, the budget of the victims was 137 dead, including three children, and 152 wounded. The investigators found two assault rifles and a large amount of ammunition on the spot.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Since yesterday there have been commemorative events in several cities, reports the Tass. In St. Petersburg, spontaneous memorials appeared on the Vasilyevsky island and near the building of the Russian National Library (RNL) on the Moskovsky prospective. In Perm, residents bring flowers in the Volunteers' Square of the Urals, in Orenburg - to the stele of the Angel of Peace. Memorials also at Izhevsk, Kazan, Nizhny Novgorod, Penza, Cheboksary and Ufa. In Petrozavodsk candles are lit on the shores of Lake Onega. And in Naryan-Mar they laid flowers in the cultural center Arktika, despite the frost and wind at 20 degrees. Residents of Nalchik and Cherkessk, Pyatigorsk and Makhachkala have descended into the street with flowers and toys.
&nbsp;
In Beslan, a commemorative event was held yesterday in the school captured by militants 20 years ago. In Simferopol, a written "Moscow, weep" was arranged with candles on the central square.
<h2> White House, "Isis solely responsible for attack"</h2>
"Isis is solely responsible for attacking the Moscow concert hall, there is no involvement of Ukraine." The US National Security Council spokesman Adrienne Watson said this in a note, which also confirmed that the US "shared with Russia information about a planned terrorist attack in the capital".
&nbsp;
<h2>Isis publishes video on the attack></h2>
Isis released a one-minute and a half-minute video with a sequence of its brutal terrorist attack in a concert hall on the outskirts of Moscow. The images, accompanied and introduced by an Arabic message "exclusive for the agency Amaq that shows moments of the bloody attack against Christians yesterday in Moscow", dated Saturday 23, were sent by the main propaganda channel of the IIS and began to circulate through the Telegram and WhatsApp channels, as well as on social networks like X. In the video, particularly raw, you see one of the terrorists shooting with an automatic weapon through a door and kills at least one person. Behind the door you see a corridor with different people on the ground and blood. Always the images show another knife-armed terrorist who approaches a wounded man lying on the ground and hits him several times on the neck, then turns to the camera and makes a speech: "Allah is the greatest, the unfaithful are defeated with the will of Allah. Let us go out on the way of Allah and give victory to their religion." Yesterday Amaq had also released an image of the four alleged authors of the Friday attack, of which at least three are seen in today's video.&nbsp;
